cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper proposes a method for learning binary representations for deep neural networks, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of deep neural networks suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a likely category. The experiments involve image datasets, indicating relevance to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the interpretation of binary neurons, which suggests relevance to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of deep neural networks for classification tasks suggests relevance to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the use of language models, which suggests relevance to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
